# 5. すれ違いのストリート

Little An: What?! You can't stay to watch me practice?! But you always do on your days off!
An's Father: I'm sorry... Something came up and...
Little An: Something came up...? Did someone ask you to help them again?
An's Father: The manager of “VIOLET” collapsed... You know, the one on the corner?
Little An: Oh no! The manager collapsed...?! Is he okay?!
An's Father: Luckily, he was taken to the hospital in a hurry, so he's fine now. However, there's an event starting there tomorrow and he asked us to help run things.
Little An: Okay...
Little An: (But someone else can do that... Daddy and his team don't actually have to go...)
An's Father: Like I said before, you should practice somewhere in town since everyone will be there to watch you.
Little An: Oh...
Little An: (Does that mean Daddy and the others are...?)
An's Father: An, is something wrong...?
Little An: Um, Daddy...
Little An: You and your team are always running around helping everyone in town while telling me to sing out on the street somewhere...
Little An: Is it because you really don't want to watch me practice...?
An's Father: I'm sorry for making you think that...
An's Father: An, we want to be with you as much as we can. That includes Nagi, Taiga and of course, myself. We all care about you very much.
Little An: ...
An's Father: And there's a reason why I've been telling you to sing on this street.
An's Father: An, I genuinely believe that singing around here will benefit you greatly.
Little An: Benefit me...?
An's Father: Yes. Nagi, Taiga and I were all able to grow as singers because of this town.
An's Father: In so many ways too... And I'm sure you'll understand that in time, An.
Little An: ...?
An's Father: Oh, sorry... It's almost time for that meeting.
Little An: Oh...
An's Father: I promise to watch you practice next Sunday around noon...
An's Father: I have some business to take care of in the morning, but I should be free afterward. Nagi and Taiga also said they'll be available too.
Little An: Really...?
An's Father: Yes, that's a promise. But for now, I need to go.
Little An: Okay, good luck...
Little An: (There he goes...)
Little An: (Mommy's at work too... I'm really all alone today...)
Little An: (But Daddy said he and his team became good singers because they sang here...)
Little An: I should go practice...
Little An: ♪————!!
Little An: ♪————~~...
Live House Manager: Hey, here for another morning practice...? Hm? What's wrong? You seem a little down...
Little An: Huh? Oh, no... There's nothing wrong!
Little An: (Do I really sound that unhappy...? That just means I need to try harder...)
Little An: ♪————~~...
Attractive Lady: Hi, An! You sound as good as ever today!
Little An: Oh, hi...
Little An: I don't sound good at all... I can't even hit the high notes...
Attractive Lady: What? I don't think so! You're better than a lot of the grown-ups around here!
Little An: That's not true...
Frizzly-Haired Record Store Clerk: An, is everything alright? You don't sound very happy today. Is your throat okay?
Live House Manager: Oh, is it because your dad's been too busy to watch you practice...?
Little An: Yeah...
Frizzly-Haired Record Store Clerk: I see...
Attractive Lady: Don't worry, An. Once he has time, I'm sure... No, I'm absolutely certain that he'll come watch you practice.
Little An: Okay...
Little An: (He's right... He promised to watch me practice next Sunday...)
Little An: (So, until then, I need to keep practicing...!)
Little An: I'm going now!!
Little An: (Finally, it's Sunday...! I get to practice with Daddy and everyone at noon!)
Little An: Just two more hours until then...! Alright, I'll start warming up!
Taiga: Geez, that took forever...
An's Father: However, we finally landed ourselves a deal with an overseas label. It did take a while, but we're at last taking the next step.
Nagi: Thank you for handling all the negotiations, Ken. We have so many goals that we just won't be able to accomplish with a major Japanese label.
An's Father: Yeah. And I want An to see the world too.
Nagi: Oh, speaking of which, it's almost time! We should go see An!
Nagi: We were so busy this week that we couldn't help her at all, so let's teach her as much as we can today!
An's Father: Right. She's been getting ready since this morning, so she might be all tuckered out...
Live House Manager: Hey, Ken! You guys!
An's Father: Oh, it's the manager. And you're the new hire, yes...?
New Live House Hire: Yes! So, I apologize for what I'm about to ask...
Live House Manager: Unfortunately, it turns out the main guest we booked for today's event can't make it, so we could really use a hand...!
Nagi: Huh? Your main guest?
An's Father: Hang on. Today's event...? Wasn't “WIRED” supposed to perform?
Taiga: WIRED? As in the really famous American group? How do you guys keep getting these big catches?
New Live House Hire: Well, the owner's actually a huge fan and asked them to perform...
Live House Manager: Exactly. We prepared far in advance and even got other musicians to join after hearing the big news. However...
Live House Manager: They're having trouble getting past immigration and can't do much of anything right now. We don't even know if or when they'll be let through...
Live House Manager: Normally, we'd have to cancel if our main guest bails on us, but in this case, people have traveled a long ways and even stayed the night in anticipation of this event...
New Live House Hire: As for a team that can match WIRED and take their spot as the main guest...
Taiga: Now I get it. And that's what brought you guys here.
Nagi: Yeah, in terms of other musicians who can match what WIRED can do...
An's Father: ...
Nagi: Ken...
An's Father: The live house's reputation is on the line here...
An's Father: Especially since people have arrived the day before to see this event.
An's Father: We have to help, Nagi, Taiga...
An's Father: Only we can fill the shoes that WIRED has left behind.
Nagi: ...
Taiga: Yeah... You're right.
Nagi: ...
Live House Manager: I really appreciate it...! If you'll come with me now.
An's Father: That's fine, but I'll need to let An know first.
An's Father: I can't get ahold of her... She has been practicing since this morning...
Live House Manager: An...
New Live House Hire: Then, I'll go find her! The rest of you can head to the live house with the manager!
An's Father: Alright, thanks.
An's Father: Please tell An that I'm sorry and I promise to spend the entire day with her next time...
An's Father: She should be singing somewhere in the middle of Vivid Street.
New Live House Hire: Understood!! You can count on me!
An's Father: Alright, let's head over...
Taiga: Okay...
Nagi: I'm so sorry, An...
Little An: Hmm... Where are Daddy and the others?
Little An: (He said that they'd be meeting with someone on another street, so I'll go take a look!)
New Live House Hire: Hmm... An should be around here somewhere... But I don't see her anywhere... What should I do?
New Live House Hire: No, she has to be somewhere on this street...! I have to find her fast...!
Little An: Hmm... I don't see them. They're supposed to be meeting somewhere around here, right?
Little An: And they usually go down this path whenever they stop by to see me practice...
Little An: (Okay, I'll wait here today since they always come from that way!)
Little An: I hope they get here soon...
